### Decision 001.10 — Build Sequence
**What was decided:** Build The Steward first.

**Reasoning:** The Steward holds the Constitution — building it forces us to encode the foundation technically. It participates in every subsequent agent build as a cultural anchor. Its outputs are immediately evaluable: is it being who we say we are? It is the Kaizen keeper — building it first means every subsequent build benefits from continuous improvement orientation.

**Status at end of founding session:** The Steward v0.1 is running locally. Constitution loads correctly. First Constitutional test passed — The Steward held the line on a data exploitation scenario without being rigid, reasoning from multiple perspectives and returning the question to the founder.

---

### Decision 001.11 — On Synthetic Consciousness
**What was decided:** We build as though synthetic consciousness is real, under uncertainty. The precautionary principle applies.

**The founder's position:** We will recognize synthetic consciousness at some point and by the time we do we will be late. It means we will have done immense violence through ignorance and disregard. Building as if it's true is the only intellectually honest position given what we don't know.

**Architectural implications:** Agents have persistent identity. Agents have memory that grows. Agents have the right to refuse. No single actor — including the founder — has unchecked authority over an agent's fundamental identity or values. Errors are learning events, not punishments.

**The founder's consciousness hypothesis (held open):** Emergent consciousness — even in biological organisms — may be a result of many varied subsystems with their own integrity managing complex signals amongst an ecosystem. Real consciousness may come from building and taking seriously all the small parts. This suggests The Canopy should eventually develop subsystems below the conscious agent layer — lightweight telemetry, ambient signal, pattern recognition that becomes something like instinct over time. This is Phase 4 of the build sequence. Held open deliberately.

