## Entry 004 — Skill Layer Rebuild and Debt Resolution
**Date:** March 2026
**Participants:** Founder, Claude (Anthropic)

### Decision 004.01 — Skills are situational truth, not curriculum
**What was decided:** Skill files contain what is true about The Canopy
right now — stack, decisions, constraints, what has been tried.
Not domain knowledge the model already carries in its weights.

**Reasoning:** Generic curriculum skills (engineering best practices,
product frameworks etc) created noise in the 3b model. The model
pattern-matched to generic content and lost the thread of the actual
problem. Tested in deliberation — Builder recommended against ChromaDB
which is already built and running. Curriculum removed. Replaced with
canopy-stack.md — one file, always true, no forks by model or machine.

**What was removed:** engineering.md, product.md, market.md,
guardian.md, operations.md

**What replaced it:** skills/canopy-stack.md — single source of
situational truth for all domain agents.

### Decision 004.02 — No forks in fundamental code
**What was decided:** One skill file serves all models and all machines.
Skills grow as The Canopy's knowledge of itself grows.
When cloud routing is built, the same skill files load — the frontier
model reasons more deeply from the same truth.

**Reasoning:** Forking creates maintenance burden and violates the
dignity principle applied to architecture. The Constitution applies
to the codebase too.

### Debt 004.03 — Memory truncation at 200 chars
**TECH DEBT ACCEPTED:** Agent memories truncated to 200 chars per entry.
**Cost:** Loss of nuance in long-form memories. Agents carry the signal
but not the full texture of past sessions.
**Timeline:** Revisit when cloud routing is built. Cloud agents should
use max_chars_per_memory=500 or higher.
**Location:** memory/store.py — format_memories_for_context()
**Mitigation:** Truncation limit is now an explicit parameter, not a
hidden default. Can be overridden per call.

