### Decision 011.03 — Item 3: Local inference context — confirmed, filed

**What was confirmed:** Frontier-scale local inference requires $50K–$100K hardware.
8GB M2 MacBook cannot run frontier models. Current architecture (Anthropic API as
substrate, llama3.2:3b for benchmarking) is the correct call. Apple M-series unified
memory is the right ecosystem for future local-capable models.

**Relevant for activism track:** Local models for privacy-sensitive use cases (surveillance
data, unhoused individuals' information) are feasible on commodity hardware at the 3B–7B
scale. Frontier models are not required for rights navigation, benefits letters, or
erasure request generation.

